"In trains added to Prague's integrated transports there are controllers equipped with card readers with whom they verify time and zonal validity," explained the Filip ticket control mode by the Ropid organization, which fine-tunes Prague's collective transport schedules.
Urban buses have card readers integrated into the driver's crate.
During the climb it is therefore necessary not only to show the magnetic card to the driver, but in addition you have to place the Opencard at the point determined next to the cash register.
Thus the driver verifies the validity of the loaded coupons.
"If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the loaded coupons, there is nothing easier than asking the driver for this kind of information," added Dr.pal.
Passengers who take city buses and will not remember, when the coupon expires, can again go to self-service ATMs, where coupons are loaded on the card.
Here you will see information on the validity of their documents on the device screen.
Sudeten Germans wanted a referendum from the US
The Germans of the Sudetenland in 1945 asked to include Umanava to the United States.
This results from the letter deposited in the South Bohemian Scientific Library.
If we cannot be part of Germany or Austria, we want to live at least under the patronage of the United States.
With this wish, some groups of Sudeten Germans reportedly addressed the President of the United States in 1945.
This is further evidenced by the letter kept in a private archive and now deposited in the South Bohemian Scientific Library.
The Germans of Cheskh Krumlov ask in the letter to the American president not to allow the return of the "district of Chemava" – occupied by Hitler under the Munich agreement – to Czechoslovakia again.
"We have understood the situation and we want to be sure of the promises that American units will arrive at German territory not as oppressors and enemies, but as liberators," the letter signed with the words "People who care about the fate of Umanava with all their heart."
