I don't believe that.
Two aspects of the structure of the brain make it difficult for us to convey our feelings towards animals.
On the one hand, it often connects the lateral prefrontal cortex with human awareness, the associated circuits (this is due to its direct participation in short memory and executive and control functions).
In humans this large area is much more developed than in other primates and it seems that among other creatures it is completely lacking.
