The witness specified that around 4:30 p.m. Locklear "crushed the accelerator thoroughly, making a lot of noise, and trying to get the car out of the parking lot with abrupt back-and-forth maneuvers. Backwards, it passed several times in front of its sunglasses."
Shortly thereafter, the witness, who apparently did not recognize the actress at first glance, saw that Locklear had stopped in a nearby road and exited the vehicle.
It was this person who alerted the emergency services, because "she was worried about Locklear's life."
When the police patrol arrived, she found the actress sitting inside her vehicle, which partially blocked the road.
"She seemed confused," and that's why officers took her to a drug and alcohol use specialist center to test her.
According to a police spokesman, the actress proved to be cooperative and the excess alcohol hypothesis was discarded from the beginning, although "according to what was observed by the officers at first, we believe that Locklear was under the influence of some drug."
Locklear was arrested on suspicion of driving under the influence of some unspecified substance and was locked up in the local prison around 7 p.m., to be released a few hours later.
Two months ago, Locklear had come out of a specialist clinic in Arizona after being hospitalized following an episode of anxiety and depression.
