The 15 million budget allocated in full by the Community of Madrid represented for Garci a "unique opportunity" to recreate the appropriate sets and costumes to portray a "studded Spain that mistaken the choice of leader to fight for and the fact that the struggle for independence brought the people a huge delay in development under the reign of Ferdinand VII" Garci noted.
However, the director regrets that he did not receive funding equal to those of Alatriste or Los phantasmos de Goya - more than twice as much as Sangre de mayo, so it was not possible to shoot some scenes provided by the set design that he himself had signed with Horacio Valcarcel, a collaborator of almost his entire career.
This, for the director of Volver a empezar, influenced what is his usual work practice, the staging with the actors, with whom he often uses to try before shooting together with those who will not be part of the cast, because he considers it "humiliating," considering that "part of the director's work lies in going to the theater and the cinema to know what is happening in the sector in which he works."
Many of the performers, part of whom are cast in Sangre de mayo, try out in front of his car, as in the case of Michael Rell, Carlos Larranaga or Fernando Guillen Cuervo.
Nominated for the Oscar four times - winning one - Garci believes that none of the three films nominated to represent Spain this year at the Hollywood Academy - his Sangre de mayo, Siete mesas de billar francés and, the last selected Los sunflowers ciegos -, do not represent the younger generation of Spanish cinema "which should instead be known."
Garci does not expect any awards from this film.
