The prices of domestic industrial sales in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - informs the Hungarian Central Statistical Institute.
Industry export sales prices compared to July 2008 were 1.1% higher, compared to the previous year they fell by 3.9%
As a result of the domestic and export price change, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than in the previous month and 3.2% higher than in a year ago.
Domestic industrial sales prices compared to the previous month increased by only 0.1%.
Domestic sales prices in the processing sector also rose to a minimum, 0.1%, compared to July.
The biggest increase in prices in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and shoe production with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastics and chemicals has caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the chemicals and products sector.
A fall in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum in woodworking (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing activities have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry, prices rose by between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector, prices increased in August by 0.3% in domestic industrial sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the gas price increase made by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared in 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the processing industry sectors, the largest increases were in the oil product processing sector (32.4%).
In the manufacture of products from metalworking, the price increase was 13.2%, 11% in the production of food, drink and tobacco, representing a decisive weight.
Prices fell in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the processing industry the pace of price increases varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total in the processing industry in the past year prices rose by 10.2%.
The electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector's prices exceeded last year's by 18.7%.
In domestic sales among target groups of sectors, the largest monthly price increase occurred in August in sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods prices grew by 0.3%, in the energy sector and in subsequent use prices did not change compared to those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the largest price increase was observed in the energy and later-use sector (16.8%).
In sectors producing consumer items the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
Industrial export sales prices calculated in guilders grew in August by 1.1% compared to the previous month, compared in 12 months they fell by 3.9%.
