Every day, in Italy, 2,500 accidents occur at work, 3 people die and 27 remain permanently disabled.
For 2007, Inail data confirm that there were about 1,200 white deaths.
Figures that testify to the severity of a phenomenon that remains a major cause of death and causes almost twice as many deaths as murders.
